observations.recommendation:
We recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to strictly adhere to COA Circular No. 97-002, mandating the liquidation of all cash advances within the prescribed timeframe and their closure at the end of each fiscal year. This will prevent the accumulation of unliquidated balances in the future;
To promptly deduct the outstanding amount from the monthly salaries of those still in service upon the terms agreed upon by the Municipality and the respective employee; and
To submit complete documentation to support the write-off of various Advances to Officers and Employee Accounts for the Auditor to thoroughly assess the validity of the write-off request, verify the circumstances rendering these advances uncollectible, and ensure compliance with all applicable accounting principles and government regulations.
